main event: A mysterious object landed in 40 feet of water and mud near the Midway gravel pit just off the Seattle-Tacoma Freeway on December 19, 1962.
interesting points: Welder John Liedtke saw a lot of sparks flying from the object, which he initially thought was a car in trouble.
The object then exploded into a big ball of fire, and the area was covered in thick smoke.
The police found a perfectly round hole, 15 feet across, in the mud where the object had landed.
The report did not provide details on the physical description of the object before it exploded, nor indicate if there was a search for debris in the pit.
The Seattle Post-Intelligencer newspaper reported the incident but did not provide additional information.
